A DNS server is used to resolve domain names of file systems' shared paths. The DNS server
IP address is 100.125.4.25.
By default, the IP address of the DNS server used to resolve domain names of file systems'
shared paths is automatically configured on ECSs when creating ECSs. No manual
configuration is needed except when the resolution fails due to a change in the DNS server IP
address.


SuSE:

weixiongchang2018:/home/linux# cat /etc/resolv.conf
### /etc/resolv.conf file autogenerated by netconfig!
#
# Before you change this file manually, consider to define the
# static DNS configuration using the following variables in the
# /etc/sysconfig/network/config file:
#     NETCONFIG_DNS_STATIC_SEARCHLIST
#     NETCONFIG_DNS_STATIC_SERVERS
#     NETCONFIG_DNS_FORWARDER
# or disable DNS configuration updates via netconfig by setting:
#     NETCONFIG_DNS_POLICY=''
#
# See also the netconfig(8) manual page and other documentation.
#
# Note: Manual change of this file disables netconfig too, but
# may get lost when this file contains comments or empty lines
# only, the netconfig settings are same with settings in this
# file and in case of a "netconfig update -f" call.
#
### Please remove (at least) this line when you modify the file!
search openstacklocal
nameserver 100.125.4.25
nameserver 8.8.8.8
weixiongchang2018:/home/linux #


weixiongchang2018:/home/linux# mkdir /testdir
weixiongchang2018:/home/linux# mount sfs-nas1.eu-de.otc.t-systems.com:/share-d7520f16 /wei
